Brazil Wins WTO Approval to Discuss Exchange Rates, Valor Says

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-05-11T12:16:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/brazil-wins-wto-approval-to-discuss-exchange-rates-valor-says.html
Brazil  won the approval of a World
Trade Organization working group to discuss the impact of
exchange rates on international trade, Valor Economico newspaper
 reported , citing an interview with Brazilian Ambassador to the
WTO Roberto Azevedo.  The group rejected a second proposal by Brazil to discuss
possible measures because of opposition from the U.S.,  China ,
the European Union and  Chile , Azevedo said, according to the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
 idantas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  